at extra setup is necessary. The library's name, \\\"Git Executable Impl,\\\" and its documentation indicate it executes git commands, so I should take that into account.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Identifying potential risks**\\n\\nI'm considering that using external CLI invocations might be unpredictable, especially if the user's configuration isn't properly set up. It's best to avoid relying on network URLs for this reason. Maybe I should cite some research in the summary to back this up. Also, I'll keep in mind that the output should be in JSON format without markdown since that's a specific requirement. I want to ensure everything is clear and accurate.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"No extra Maven dependencies or Docker service are needed. The artifact is the Maven SCM Git executable provider and depends only on normal transitive Maven SCM/Plexus/Commons libraries; meaningful end-to-end command coverage, if attempted, requires a local Git repository initialized by the test.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Prefer updating the existing command-construction/consumer tests for the 1.11.1 API change. If exercising real provider commands rather than only static command builders, create a temporary local git repository or bare file:// remote in the test, run git init, configure user.name and user.email locally, and create an initial commit before invoking Maven SCM GitExe operations. Avoid network remotes.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Tests that execute git depend on the git executable being available on PATH.\",\n    \"Real git command tests can be flaky unless they use only temp directories, local file:// remotes, and local repository config.\",\n    \"The compile failure shown is an API signature change in GitTagCommand.createCommandLine requiring the new boolean sign parameter, not a missing dependency or service.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":